servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
---

Pre-heat your oven to 180 degrees. Slice the @butternut squash{1} in half lengthways
and scoop out the seeds. Slice it widthways to about 1cm thick (we want to be able
to cook this nice and quickly). Now chop it into 1cm cubes.

Place on a #baking tray{}, drizzle butternut with @olive oil{}, the @chilli flakes{1/2} to
taste and the leaves of the @thyme{4}(leaves, stalks discarded). Season with a
pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Place in your oven and cook
for about ~{20%minutes}, or until your squash is soft (you can easily slip a knife
through) and crisp on the outside.

In the meantime, get the delicious dressing and salad ready. Chop the
@cucumber{1/2} in half lengthways and then in half again. Now chop into ½cm cubes.

Mix the @tahini{3} with a good squeeze of @lemon{1/2}(juiced) and a good splash of
@olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Feel free to adjust to
your own taste. It should have a wonderful deep nutty flavour.

Pop the @sunflower seeds{1} into a #frying pan{} (without any oil) and put on low
heat for about ~{5%minutes}, shaking the pan every now and then to turn them.
> You are toasting these to make them extra tasty. Watch them like a hawk - the
> last thing you want is for them to burn!

In a #bowl{}, crumble the @feta cheese{3/4} over the @dried cranberries{0.3},
add the @baby watercress{1}, chopped cucumber, toasted sunflower seeds and cover
with three-quarters of your tahini dressing. Give this a good toss.

Plate up by placing your warm butternut squash over your watercress and cranberry
salad. Drizzle your remaining dressing on top.